  "body": "[comment]: # (Please replace ... with your information. Remove < and >)\r\n\r\n### User Story\r\n\r\nAs a user, I want to see the fiat value of assets so that I know value.\r\n\r\n### Description\r\n\r\n[comment]: # (Feature or Bug? i.e Type: Bug)\r\n*Type*: Feature\r\n\r\n[comment]: # (Describe the feature you would like, or briefly summarise the bug and what you did, what you expected to happen, and what actually happens. Sections below)\r\n*Summary*: \r\n\r\nThe asset list in the wallet only shows the ETH/token amount, but it can be hard to know the value of `0.0034` ETH. Let's bring confidence and clarity here by showing the fiat amount.\r\n\r\n#### Expected behavior\r\nA user looking at the asset list can see the fiat value.\r\n\r\n#### Actual behavior\r\nA user is oblivious of asset list value\r\n\r\n\r\n### Solution\r\n[comment]: # (Please summarise the solution and provide a task list on what needs to be fixed.)\r\n*Summary*: \r\n\r\nShow the fiat value next to the crypto amount.\r\n\r\n<img width=\"219\" alt=\"show-fiat\" src=\"https://user-images.githubusercontent.com/116099/39290576-5abcd3b6-4930-11e8-9e26-6c24362ff447.png\">\r\n",
